  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to compare the functional, clinical and radiographic outcomes
      associated with trans-articular drilling versus retro-articular drilling, two commonly
      employed techniques of operative treatment for stable forms of juvenile osteochondritis
      dissecans (JOCD) lesions. This study also aims to better define the natural history of this
      condition in its most commonly identified pathological state (as a stable lesion) following
      surgical intervention by determining the rate of radiographic healing and any need for
      secondary surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
